Nigerian rapper Falz The Bahd Guy, real name Folarin Falana, has opened an ongoing debate in Nigeria and all over the world with his remake of Donald Glover's (Childish Gambino) This is America. He dropped his now viral This is Nigeria music video over the weekend, and the rapperâ€™s boldness has become one of the most discussed topics in the Nigerian music space, as people continue to share their opinion on the subjects raised by his adaptation of the song. The video caught the attention of Bad Boy Records founder Sean ''Diddy'' Combs. Diddy applauded Falz for his effort with the Instagram caption: "#Nigeria LETS GO!!!!! Sending love to Nigeria. So many great, beautiful artist changing the game!!!!''